      <entry xml:id="entry_ozgalun" xml:lang="os-x-digor" abv:completeness="incomplete">
        <form type="lemma"><orth>ozgalun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>ozgald</orth><form
              type="variant" subtype="parens"><orth>wozgalun</orth></form></form></form>
        <usg><lang/></usg>
        <sense xml:lang="os-x-digor"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
            <q>взглянуть, посмотреть (косо)</q>
          </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
            <q>take a look, look sideways</q>
          </abv:tr></sense>
        <abv:exampleGrp>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>æ falʒostæ raozgaluj æfsærmitæj</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>она осматривается вокруг стыдливо</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>she looks around shyly</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sam."/>
              <biblScope>115</biblScope></bibl>
          </abv:example>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>ajdænæmæ raozgalgæj dæ bor ʒikkotæ du fastaj</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>поглядывая в зеркало, ты расчесывала свои русые косы</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>looking in the mirror, you combed your blond braids</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Тайм._Мӕ_зӕрд."/>
              <biblScope>42</biblScope></bibl>
          </abv:example>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>Sajnægi furt Alij sæmæ raozgælddæltæ kodta ma kizgæj dær, osæj dær banælwægutæ
              ʽncæ</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>сын Сайнага Али кинул на них косые взгляды, и они, девушки и женщины, попадали в
                обморок</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>the son of Saynag Ali cast sidelong glances at them, and they, girls and women,
                fainted</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/>
              <biblScope>II 22</biblScope></bibl>
          </abv:example>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>bæxi mardæj Murǧuzi rasorun fændæ iskodton; fal mæmæ ǧuntʼuz Murǧuz togʒastæj
              raozgaldta</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>я решил отогнать Мургуза (собаку) от лошадиного трупа, но хмурый Мургуз взглянул на
                меня налитыми кровью глазами</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>I decided to drive Murguz (the dog) away from the horse's corpse, but the gloomy
                Murguz looked at me with bloodshot eyes</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/>
              <biblScope>1958 III 29</biblScope></bibl>
          </abv:example>
        </abv:exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, из <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
            >ava-skal-</w></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
            <w>scheel</w>
            <gloss><q>косой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>schielen</w>
            <gloss><q>смотреть косо</q></gloss></mentioned>; к <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">skel-</w>
            <gloss><q>кривой</q>, <q>косой</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
            <w>οϰολιος</w></mentioned> и пр.) Развитие значения <q>косой</q> — <q>косой взгляд</q>,
            <q>косо смотреть</q> как в <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
            <w>scheel</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>schielen</w></mentioned> или
            <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
            <w>obliquus</w>
            <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">(<quote>oculo obliquo aspicere</quote>)</note><note
              xml:lang="en" type="comment">(<quote>oculo obliquo
            aspicere</quote>)</note></mentioned>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">Probably from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
            >ava-skal-</w></mentioned>, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
            <w>scheel</w>
            <gloss><q>sidelong</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>schielen</w>
            <gloss><q>look sideways</q></gloss></mentioned>; к <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">skel-</w>
            <gloss><q>curve</q>, <q>sidelong</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
            <w>οϰολιος</w></mentioned> and so on.) The development of the meaning <q>sidelong</q> —
            <q>sideways glance</q>, <q>look sideways</q> like in <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
            <w>scheel</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>schielen</w></mentioned> or
            <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
            <w>obliquus</w>
            <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">(<quote>oculo obliquo aspicere</quote>)</note><note
              xml:lang="en" type="comment">(<quote>oculo obliquo
            aspicere</quote>)</note></mentioned>.</etym>
      </entry>
